reviews.review_text: NIce Show Clean SB of an upbeat show
Brent in prime time dialed in & polished smoothly

another great Charlie Miller remastered SB ! The guy below me said it just right..   Show's like this one, me make me love the Brent era more than any other.  I think this show contains my absolute favorite "Feel like a stranger".   Jerry is just on fire, and Brent's tickling the ivories weaving an elaborate tapestry in between Jerry's notes.  Phil's bass and Bill/Mick's drums thumping away underneath it all, and Bob chiming in at the right moments with some extra goodness.   It's great to stream, but if you'd like to know how you can (easily) snag the entire show- shoot me an email at sticknails@aol.com.... 

5 stars from me-  for the performance, and the absolutely beautiful sound quality.

i love this show first set is good, the second set is great... am always partial to high energy chuck berry stuff to end a show.

beautiful, pristine remastered sbd.

Philly 4 Shot It was fun to get a 4 night run in Philly at a different venue. it seemed like the Hilton across the street had a hundred of my fiends staying. Right by U Penn campus, made for interesting energy, good times. Sound quality here is tremendous!
Philly Run  This whole 3 night Philly run doesn't have a bad show in it!? That's rare for any year. I can pick any night this spring tour at this venue and there all great!!!!
